default.1
default              
defaultThe
default lines of accountability for local decision making on transport expenditure in terms of the South East Local Enterprise Partnership (SELEP) and Transport Body (SELTB) are not clear. As 
defaultpreviously described, the role of the LTB in relation to the LEP is unc
defaultlear and both the LTB and the LEP are not accountable to an electorate, rather each local authority within the LTB and LEP is accountable to its own electorate
default. There is
default no 
defaultpublic 
defaultaccountability governing the business element of the LEP
default.
default&#xa0;
default6.2
default              
defaultThere needs t
defaulto be clear lines of accountability when it comes to decision making on all expenditure. Local authorities are able to do this 
defaultwith the transparent decision making processes that they implement with the Cabinet system which includes Cabinet Committees, Cabi
defaultnet Member, Leader of the Council and full Council decisions. 
defaultCouncils are ultimatel
defaulty accountable to the public
default they serve
default and through the democratic process the public can vote for new representation 
defaultwithin the electoral cycle if they are not satisfied wi
defaultth the decisions being made on their behalf.
default&#xa0;
default6.3
default              
defaultHowever, with the curr
defaultent proposals for devolved local decision making on transport expenditure being implemented post 2015, there is a
default clear lack of accountability in
default both the LEP and the LTB. Given the di
defaultfficulty of agreeing consensus on transport priorities within the LTB and LEP
default,
default with each local authority seek
defaulting to promote schemes that
default benefit their individual areas, the method of how overall decisions are made and the accountability of that decision ma
defaultking process 
defaultis brought into question. LEP business representatives also have a say in the decision making process yet they are not democratically accountable.
default&#xa0;
default6.4
default              
defaultDecisions taken on transport expenditure by the LTB and the LEP do not have clear lines of 
defaultaccountability and 
defaultas such 
defaultdevolved funding 
defaultshould
default be given direct to
default federated LEP areas
default. This will allow
default local authorities
